-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
pybgpdump 0.2
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Jon Oberheide <jon@oberheide.org>
  http://jon.oberheide.org/projects/pybgpdump

DESCRIPTION

  pybgpdump combines the functionality of libbgpdump and the ease of python to
  parse BGP messages from MRT dumps.

FEATURES

  * currently support for IPv4 BGP4MP_MESSAGE and BGP4MP_MESSAGE_32BIT_AS
  * supports uncompressed, gzip'ed, and bzip2'ed files transparently
  * includes sample programs, such as route_btoa.py

INSTALL

  make
  make install

DOCUMENTATION

  See the samples directory.

DEPENDENCIES

  pybgpdump depends on the MRT and BGP modules of dpkt (SVN/1.7) which can be
  found here: http://www.monkey.org/~dugsong/dpkt/

